 When you call someone who is thousands of miles away, you use a satellite.
 The satellite in space receives the call and then reflects it almost immediately back down to the ground.
 The satellite was launched into space by a rocket. Scientists use telescopes in space because the earth's atmosphere distorts our light and our view a little.
 It takes a giant rocket with a height of more than 100 feet to shoot a satellite or a telescope into space.
