 Since Auckland stretches over two harbours, there are many beaches. The most popular beaches are in three areas.
 The beaches of North Shore (in the district of North Harbour) are located on the Pacific Ocean and extend from Long Bay in the north to Devonport in the south.
 Almost all are sandy beaches with safe swimming and most provide shade, which is provided by Pohutukawa trees.
 The beaches of Tamaki Drive are located at the port of Waitemata, in the upscale suburbs of Mission Bay and St. Heliers in Central Auckland.
 There are family beaches, which are sometimes overcrowded, with a beautiful shopping promenade along the coast. Swimming is safe here.
 The most important local beer is "Number One". It is not a complex beer, but pleasant and refreshing. The other local beer is called "Manta".
 There are many French wines to drink, but the New Zealand and Australian wines are perhaps more palatable.
 The local tap water is safe to drink, but if you are concerned, bottled water is also readily available.
 "For Australians, the idea of a coffee ""Flat White"" is foreign. A small espresso is ""espresso"", cappuccino is filled high with milk (not foam) and tea is served without milk."
 The hot chocolate is Belgian standard. Fruit juices are expensive, but excellent.
 Many diving trips take place throughout the year and injuries due to any of these causes on the reef are rare.
 However, you should follow the advice of authorities, pay attention to all signs and, in particular, pay attention to safety warnings.
 Squid occur in the vicinity of beaches and near river mouths from October to April north of 1770. They can occasionally occur outside of this time frame.
 Sharks exist, but they rarely attack humans. Most sharks are afraid of humans and would swim away.
 Saltwater crocodiles do not live actively in the sea, their primary habitat is in river mouths north of Rockhampton.
 A booking in advance gives the traveler the assurance that he will have a place to stay when he arrives at his destination.
 Travel agencies often have arrangements with specific hotels, although you may also be able to book other accommodation, such as camping, through a travel agency.
 Travel agencies usually offer packages that include breakfast, transportation to and from the airport, or even a combination of flight and hotel.
 You can also hold your reservation for you, in case you need time to reconsider the offer or to get additional documents for your travel destination (e.g. visa).
 Any changes or queries should be directed to the travel agency and not directly to the hotel.
