 Whoever wants to drive in high latitudes or over mountain passes should reckon with snow, ice and temperatures below freezing.
 On icy and snowy roads, liability is low and one cannot drive as if one were on bare asphalt.
 In snowstorms, so much snow can fall in a very short time that one can get stuck.
 The visibility can also be impaired by falling or blowing snow or by condensation or ice on the vehicle windows.x
 On the other hand, icy and snowy conditions are normal in many countries, and traffic runs almost continuously throughout the year.
 Safaris are perhaps the biggest tourist attraction in Africa and the highlight for many visitors.
 The term safari in common usage refers to a land trip to observe the overwhelming African wildlife, especially in the savannah.
 Some animals, such as elephants and giraffes, tend to approach cars closely, and the standard equipment allows a good view.
 Lions, cheetahs and leopards are often shy and you can see them better with a pair of binoculars.
 A foot safari (also called bushwalk, trek or footing) is a hike that lasts either a few hours or several days.
