 In most monasteries there are indeed wrap dresses for women who come unprepared, but if you bring your own, especially one in bright colors, the monk or nun at the entrance will give you a smile.
 Similarly, men must wear pants that reach the knees.
 These can also be borrowed from the entrance, but the clothes are not washed after each user, so you may not feel comfortable in these dresses. For all men there is a standard size!
 The cuisine of Mallorca is based, as in similar areas of the Mediterranean, on bread, vegetables and meat (especially pork) and always uses olive oil.
 A simple popular dinner, especially in the summer, is Pa amb Oli: Bread with olive oil, tomatoes and any available ingredient such as cheese, tuna, etc.
 "All nouns start with a capital letter next to the word you for ""you"" always, even in the middle of a sentence."
 This is an important way to distinguish between some verbs and objects.
 It makes reading easier, but writing is somewhat difficult because one has to determine whether a verb or a noun is used as the main word.
 Italian pronunciation is relatively easy, as most words are pronounced exactly as they are written.
 The most important letters to pay attention to are c and g, as their pronunciation varies depending on the following vowel.
 "Also, pay attention to the difference between r and rr: caro means "love", while carro means "chariot.""
